cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE

This paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on determining the referents of noun phrases in Japanese sentences. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to achieve its goal, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also mentions precision and recall rates, indicating the use of statistical models, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with information retrieval, which is covered under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper uses a method that involves the use of modifiers and possessors of noun phrases, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
